{
  "texts": [
    "Table 2 shows examples of ambiguous columns from the BIRD benchmark.",
    "Ambiguous schemas can lead models to select the wrong tables or columns in their generated SQL queries, as language models typically use semantic similarity for schema linking.",
    "Fortunately, databases usually provide informative comments for ambiguous schema.",
    "We incorporate these comments into both the input of the schema item classifier and the database prompts to facilitate the LLM to perform accurate schema linking.",
    "In Figure 4, we show a training sample from the Spider benchmark, consisting of paired input and output sequences."
  ]
}